# Hi! I'm Angi
I'm a career changer, moving from hospitality to cybersecurity. I helped to manage a small motel before getting my own vacation rental business. Burnout required me to change some things, so I took a hard look at my life. Like many, I took some time during COVID to decide what I wanted to do with the rest of my life. I learned a little HTML and CSS on freecodecamp, data science with IBM, and eventually found cybersecurity. 
I made my 5 year plan, sold my business, and went back to school. I had a LOT to catch up on. Not only did I need to learn how to secure a system, but I had to learn how the darn thing worked in the first place. What's worse is the more I learn , the more I realize I don't know. So, rather than trying to learn it all, I'm doing my best to have a high level understanding of most things. That said, there are a few things that I really enjoy doing, and those are the ones I'm going to get better at!
